<html>
<h1> SPARQL Request</h1> 
<p>This SPARQL request will show me the drugs targetting specific genes.<br>
To be more precise, these results will answer the question:<br>
<em>What are drugs targeting genes linked to autosomal recessive distal spinal muscular atrophy 2?</em><br>
However, at this stage, I will first try to retrieve a list of drugs. </p>

<head>
<!-- Initialize a global WBK function -->
<script src="https://cdn.rawgit.com/maxlath/wikidata-sdk/dist/dist/wikibase-sdk.min.js"></script>
<!-- Initialize a global wdk object using the WBK object -->
<script src="https://cdn.rawgit.com/maxlath/wikidata-sdk/dist/dist/wikidata-sdk.min.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
  <pre id="output"></pre>
 
  <script>
    query = `SELECT ?drugLabel ?genessmaLabel ?proteinLabel 
    WHERE {?drug wdt:P231 ?cas.
    ?genessma wdt:P2293* wd:Q16944450.
    ?genessma wdt:P688 ?protein.
    ?drug wdt:P129 ?protein.
    SERVICE wikibase:label { bd:serviceParam wikibase:language '[AUTO_LANGUAGE],en'. } 
    }`
    fetch(
      wdk.sparqlQuery(query)
    ).then( response => response.json()
    ).then( wdk.simplify.sparqlResults
    ).then(
      function (response) {
      
		/*uncomment the next 2 lines, and comment the code for the html table to output the query in a json format
    Leave the { and the ) at line 52 and 53 */
    /*       document.getElementById('output').innerHTML =
          JSON.stringify(response, undefined, 2); */
          
		  /* this next bit of code creates an html table*/
    var html = "<table>";
    html += "<tr>";
    html += "<td>Gene</td>";
    html += "<td>Drug</td>";
    html += "</tr>";
    for(var i=0; i< response.length;i++) {
    html += "<tr>";
    html += "<td>"+response[i].genessmaLabel+"</td>";
    html += "<td>"+response[i].drugLabel+"</td>";
    html += "</tr>";
    }
    html += "</table>"
     document.getElementById('output').innerHTML = html;
     
      }
    ) 
  </script>

</body>
